{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Reorganize Content Directory Structure for Multilingual CMS Support\n\nAudit and restructure the content directory to ensure Polish language pages are correctly placed in the 'pl' subdirectory for proper CMS functionality.\n\nRequirements:\n- Scan the content directory to identify all Polish language pages currently located outside the 'pl' folder\n- Move all Polish pages to content/pl/ maintaining their relative structure\n- Verify other language pages are also in their correct language-specific directories\n- Update any internal references or links that point to the moved files\n- Check CMS configuration to confirm it expects this directory structure\n- Test CMS functionality after reorganization to ensure pages are properly detected and editable\n- Document the correct directory structure convention for future content additions\n\nEdge cases to consider:\n- Pages with mixed language content or translation pairs\n- Asset references (images, files) that may use relative paths\n- URL routing that may depend on file location\n- Build process dependencies on specific directory structures",
